To some extent, by assisting in tracking the information on a specific person, the cookies and location data could be deemed as&nbsp;tools preinstalled on the users’ computers for collecting, storing and using their personal information, which may disclose his / her private life, e.g. hobbies, favourite websites and locations usually visited by him / her.
As such, it is currently understood that all rules on data protection are applicable to cookies as well as location data. For example, cyberspace service provider must seek for users’ prior acceptance before some certain technologies (e.g. cookies, positioning service) are activated.Last modified 10 Jan 2022
				
			